    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Exterior Light Monitor</title>
        <para>To remove the exterior light check monitor, locate the four mounting screws securing the monitor to the
            front bulkhead over the driver position (
            <hotlnk document="s47005_25.xml" xrefid="f4700574">Fig. 74</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the four mounting screws.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully remove the light check monitor.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the connecting harness plugs from the monitor.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the plugs and remove monitor.</para>
            <figure id="f47005178" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g47005178.webp" filename="../figg47/G47005178.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 178. Exterior Light Monitor Harness Connections</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVER LIGHT BAR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EXTERNAL LIGHT MONITOR HARNESS CONNECTORS</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EXTERNAL LIGHT MONITOR MOUNTING SCREW HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EXTERNAL LIGHT MONITOR HEADER HARNESS ACCESS OPENING</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVER OVERHEAD FRONT BULKHEAD</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EXTERNAL LIGHT MONITOR SCREW ATTACHMENT MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
